Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
flipModule(25.10)                                            flipModule(25.10)

Name
       flipModule

Syntax
       flipModule

       [-help]

       <moduleName>

       {<X> | <Y>}

       Flips  all hierarchical instances in the specified module, with respect
       to the referenced X axis or Y axis of the module. Use this command  af-
       ter importing the design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each flipModule parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man flipModule

       <moduleName>
              Specifies the name of the module  whose  hierarchical  instances
              are to be flipped.

              Data_type: string, required

       <X> | <Y>
              Specifies  the  X or Y axis of the module to be used as a refer-
              ence to flip all hierarchical instances. This referenced X or  Y
              axis is normally at the center of the module.

              Data_type: enum, required

Example
       The  following  command  flips all hierarchical instances in the module
       DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST from the right side of the referenced  Y  axis
       to  the  left  and  from  the left side to the right, and flips all in-
       stances mirrored through it's own Y axis as well.

       flipModule DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST Y

       Before:
       After

